text: Homadaula punctigera is a moth in the family Galacticidae. It was described by Rebel in 1910. It is found in the Alai Mountains in Central Asia. The wingspan is about 16 mm. Adults are dark greyish, with black scales. The hindwings are dark grey.Neue palaearktische Pyraliden, Tortriciden und Tineen ==References== Category:Moths described in 1910 Category:Galacticidae
